summary: on their first day at high school, tony stark decides that natasha romanoff is a mystery wrapped in an enigma wrapped in a tight...
body:
on their first day at high school, tony stark decides that natasha romanoff is a mystery wrapped in an enigma wrapped in a tight leather jacket, and that he’ll figure her out or die trying.

two years later, he’s still working on it.

he’s stubborn, natasha will give him that. persistent. he offers her a seat with his friends, the phone number of his cousin sharon who he’s sure she would adore, so many opportunities to become close, all of which she rejects.

she doesn’t have anything against him - natasha simply has already fulfilled her necessary friend quota (maximum number: two), and has no need to get to know half of the school through tony.

it’s not until he mentions the avengers, the name slipping out before he can stop himself, that she becomes interested.

“what’s the avengers?” she asks, arms crossed as she leans against her locker, her expression carefully neutral to hide her curiosity.

he looks surprised that she’s actually taking an interest in something, though he’s also sure that it will be gone once he explains. “it’s my dungeons and dragons group,” he says. “we liked the name; it’s me, thor, bruce, steve, and sometimes clint.”

“you mean thor as in…thor odinson, blonde jock with arms bigger than my head?”

tony smiles slightly, nodding. “yeah, he’s a pretty cool guy, actually.”

natasha stares at him for a moment, a hint of amusement in her eyes, and, just when he thinks that the conversation’s over, she says, “it’s a cool name. i’ll see you at the next meeting.”

with that, she grabs her bag and leaves, tony staring after her, dumbfounded.

“but you don’t even know when-yeah, you’ll find out.” he’s pretty sure that she knows just about everything, and he still knows nothing about her.

he’ll figure her out soon enough though, just you wait and see.

blog.description: Most of the comics I read are Marvels from 1984. Every time I read a comic, I post a comment. That's pretty much it.

title: Struggle!
body:
Iron Man #178

Short story about Tony’s fight with alcoholism.

  • There’s no action. No nothing. Just solid drama as we watch Tony over the course of twelve hours. He reaches out to former friends. And tries to stay sober.
  • Being low-key makes it seem very real. And, by the end, we do feel for him.
  • Denny O'Neil (20 of 49).
  • Luke McDonnell (19 of 37). 

8/10
